Create a HTML form elements to design and implement a functional "Student Registration Form". Your form must collect the following user
inputs using appropriate elements and attributes:
(a)Full Name (b) Email Address (c) Username (d) Password (e) Gender selection (radio buttons) (f) Date of Birth 
(g) Phone Number (h)Address(multiline text area) (i)Engineering Stream (dropdown/select list) (j)Preferred subjects (checkboxes) 
(k) A "Register" button to submit the form





<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Student Registration Form</title>
</head>
<body>

<h2>Student Registration Form</h2>

<form>

Full Name:
<input type="text"><br><br>

Email Address:
<input type="email"><br><br>

Username:
<input type="text"><br><br>

Password:
<input type="password"><br><br>

Gender:
<input type="radio" name="gender"> Male
<input type="radio" name="gender"> Female
<br><br>

Date of Birth:
<input type="date"><br><br>

Phone Number:
<input type="tel"><br><br>

Address:<br>
<textarea rows="4" cols="30"></textarea><br><br>

Engineering Stream:
<select>
    <option>Computer Science</option>
    <option>Information Science</option>
    <option>Electronics</option>
    <option>Mechanical</option>
    <option>Civil</option>
</select>
<br><br>

Preferred Subjects:<br>
<input type="checkbox"> HTML
<input type="checkbox"> C
<input type="checkbox"> Java
<input type="checkbox"> Python
<br><br>

<button>Register</button>

</form>

</body>
</html>
